From 7f9eedd206426b35afe847ddf543370e49c4fc92 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 23:18:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Add -fallow-argument-mismatch for gfortran 10+
 compatibility

The global Fortran release flags include -fdefault-real-8 and
-fdefault-double-8, which promote all undeclared REAL variables to
REAL(8) (64-bit double precision) at compile time.

The legacy Fortran 77 ENSDF processing tools (alphad.f, hsicc.for,
logft.for, etc.) pass single-precision literal constants such as 0.0
to subroutines that receive REAL(8) arguments promoted by the same
flag. In gfortran < 10 this kind mismatch was silently allowed; in
gfortran >= 10 it became a hard error:

  Error: Type mismatch between actual argument at (1) and actual
  argument at (2) (REAL(8)/REAL(4)).

-fallow-argument-mismatch is gfortran's documented flag for restoring
the pre-10 permissive behaviour for exactly this class of legacy F77
code: argument kind mismatches are downgraded from errors back to
warnings, leaving the promoted-real semantics otherwise intact.

The flag is added to both Fortran release and debug flag sets so that
all ENSDF executables (alphad, delta, gtol, bldhst, hsicc, hsmrg,
seqhst, logft, radd, ruler) can compile with the conda-forge gfortran
14.3.0 toolchain.
---
 cmake/PyneMacros.cmake | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/cmake/PyneMacros.cmake b/cmake/PyneMacros.cmake
index 14bf4aee..450d4be4 100644
--- a/cmake/PyneMacros.cmake
+++ b/cmake/PyneMacros.cmake
@@ -101,9 +101,9 @@ macro(pyne_setup_fortran)
   if(Fortran_COMPILER_NAME MATCHES "gfortran.*")
     # gfortran
     set(CMAKE_Fortran_FLAGS_RELEASE
-        "-funroll-all-loops -fpic -fdefault-real-8 -fdefault-double-8")
+        "-funroll-all-loops -fpic -fdefault-real-8 -fdefault-double-8 -fallow-argument-mismatch")
     set(CMAKE_Fortran_FLAGS_DEBUG
-        "-fpic -fdefault-real-8 -fdefault-double-8")
+        "-fpic -fdefault-real-8 -fdefault-double-8 -fallow-argument-mismatch")
   elseif(Fortran_COMPILER_NAME MATCHES "ifort.*")
     # ifort (untested)
     set(CMAKE_Fortran_FLAGS_RELEASE "-f77rtl -O2 -r8")
-- 
2.53.0

